Actually the movie is not Hi-res

Reason #1, A camcorder recording a movie screen will never be hi-res, yes even if it is a hi-def camcorder.

Reason #2, The resolution of this movie is not the standard format of a 720p hi-res movie. Yes a 720p movie does have the resolution of 1280 x 720, thus the title 720. However, if you look at the dimensions of this recording it is 540 X 280, which in case you didn't know is is known as 280. 280 is the standard title given to a recording of STANDARD DEFINITION.... ie. the highest possible rating that is NOT hi-def. 

Anyways just thought I would clear that all up.
